title: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils

heading_context: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
If you’re an instructor or trainer, use this service to:

  • book theory tests
  • confirm your pupil’s details before the test
  • check appointments
  • change or cancel appointments
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content: There’s a different service to book your own theory test.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content: You must be registered to book tests. You’ll get your Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) business ID, username and password when you register to book.
chunks.plain_content:
Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
Register to book theory tests
You must be registered to book tests. You’ll get your Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) business ID, username and password when you register to book.

heading_context: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
Book and manage theory tests online
chunks.html_content:
You’ll need your:

  • Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) business ID
  • username
  • password
  • credit or debit card
  • pupil’s driving licence number if you’re confirming their details

You can book the following types of test:

  • car
  • motorcycle
  • lorry and bus, including the Driver Certificate of Professional Competence (CPC) part 1 (theory) and part 2 (case studies) tests

heading_context: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
You can book tests up to 3 months in advance. You do not have to give a pupil’s details when you book. This is known as being a ‘trainer booker’.

You must confirm the pupil’s details by 4pm at least one clear working day before the test. Working days do not include Sundays and public holidays.

chunks.html_content: Confirm the pupil’s details by 4pm on Wednesday if the test is on Friday.

heading_context: Book and manage theory tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
You must give at least 3 full working days’ notice to change or cancel the test, or you’ll have to pay again. Monday to Saturday count as working days but Sundays and public holidays do not.

Find out when you can get a refund if you change a theory test or cancel a theory test at short notice.
